history.text: Hello, how are you today?
I'm well
Did you enjoy watching Wonder Woman?
I did. I thought it was thrilling.
So did I. What was your favorite part?
I liked how the action scenes dealt with stopping war, so while it might have seemed cheesy, they were able to pull it off.
Did you agree with the ratings for the movie?
Yea, Gal Gadot and all the amazons on Themyscira did a really great job. It was very true to the comics.
I think 92% is probably a bit crazy, but I agree with 7.6 from the audience scores
What about you?
Yes, I think 92% is quite high, but I have to realize my bias that I'm not a huge fan of comic book movies to begin with. But, it was very good as a superhero movie.
Yea same with me. I thought it was well done even though I'm not a huge comic book person. I really liked how the movie was all tied back to the photo of her and her team during the war.
Did you have a favorite scene or scenes?
I liked the scenes when she and chris pine were sharing moments with eachother. They were generally pretty funny. What about you?
I enjoyed the beginning scenes of Amazonian island.
Yea those were beautiful. I really enjoyed the whole greek mythology theme.
Were you expecting Ares to be the bad guy at the end?
No, the whole Ares thing was new to me. Also, I didn't realize that she was created by Zeus. That wasn't really clear in the TV series with Linda Carter.
Yea, I had no idea about that part either. What did you think of Robin Wrights rols as the general of the Amazons? Do you think she pulled it off?
Yes, she is fantastic and is tailor-made for that part. I though the whole Wonder Woman storyline took place during WWII not WWI - I wonder if this was just for the movie?
Like, I thought I remember Nazis as being part of the original comic book, but the movie looks like it is set way earlier than that.

I'm not sure about that. Maybe they didn't want to make her too old? I have no idea. I liked the way the director portrayed the war scenes though. I'm usually not a fan of world war era movies. What did you think about Patty Jenkins as a director?
Yes, that was impressive. I'm glad a female director was able to direct a female-oriented superhero film. What did you think of her directorial efforts?

Yea I agree with that, I think a female was the best choice in being able to capture the feeling of an empowered female lead, especially in the current political climate. She did a great job. Do you think she will be back for the next one?
Yes, I could see her being back. Usually when a franchise starts off really well, like this movie has, they don't like to mess with the formula.
Ah, good point. Were you able to figure out that Sir Patrick was actually the bad guy? I took me a long while.
Yes, that was a nice plot twist and I didn't figure it out until it was revealed.
Same, I'm glad she finally got to use the GodKiller sword. That would have been a let down if Ares never actually showed up.
Did you think Chris Pine did a good job as the love interest in the movie?

Yeah, the whole GodKiller sword seems like she was endowed with much greater powers than I realized.I'm okay with Chris Pine. His voice sort of wears on me, but I think he did a good job. What is your opinion of Chris Pine?

Haha, I didn't really notice his voice, but I'm sure I will now. I thought he was funny. I really liked the actions scenes with him, especially the one when he went and stole that notebook from the evil scientist. Then flew away and barely escaped.
Oh, we're done. It's been a pleasure talking with you!
BYE!!

uid2response.feedback: I thought the other user was good and actively engaged.
